$ Oracle Log Writer (LGWR) background process

The *log-writer process* writes the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/redo-data/record[redo records] that are stored in the
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/redo-log-buffer[redo log buffer] (which is in the volatile memory of the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA) to the
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/online-redo-log-files[online redo log file].

LGWR is a → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/processes/background[background process].

sa:

  The `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/event_name/list/log/buffer-space` event.

  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/processes/background/ARCn
